, the Negro Astronomer|pages=79\u201384|volume=11|date=January 1863|number=63|journal=[[The Atlantic|The Atlantic Monthly]]|location=[[Boston]], [[Massachusetts]]|publisher=Ticknor & Fields|via=[[HathiTrust|HathiTrust Digital Library]]|accessdate=2019-03-21}}\n* {{cite book |last=Crew |first=Harvey W., Webb, William Bensing, Wooldridge, John |year=1892 |url=https://books.google.com/?id=5Q81AAAAIAAJ&&pg=PA87#v=onepage&q&f=false |work=Centennial History of the City of Washington, D.C. |publisher=United Brethren Publishing House |place=Dayton, Ohio |title=IV. \"Permanent Capital Site Selected\"|page=87|lccn=06028029|oclc=2843595 |accessdate=2009-05-07|via=[[Google Books]]}}\n* {{cite book |last=Jusserand|first=Jean Jules|author-link=Jean Jules Jusserand |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=u2MUAAAAYAAJ&pg=PA137#v=onepage&q&f=false |work=With Americans of Past and Present Days||oclc=1075914 |title=Major L'Enfant and the Federal City |location=New York |publisher=[[Charles Scribner's Sons]] |pages=137\u2013195 |year=1916 |accessdate=2011-08-15 |via=[[Google Books]]}}\n* {{cite book|last=Latrobe|first=John H. B., Esq.|url=https://archive.org/details/memoirbenjaminb00socigoog/page/n7/mode/1up|title=Memoir of Benjamin Banneker: Read before the Maryland Historical Society at the Monthly Meeting, May 1, 1845|location=Baltimore, Maryland|publisher=Printed by John D. Toy|year=1845|lccn=rc01003345|oclc=85791076|accessdate=February 29, 2020|via=[[Internet Archive]]}}\n* {{cite book|last=Morrison|first=Hugh Alexander|url=https://archive.org/details/preliminarycheck00morr|title=Preliminary Check List of American Almanacs: 1639-1800|work=Library of Congress|year=1907|publisher=[[United States Government Publishing Office|Government Printing Office]]|oclc=577096527|lccn=06035021|location=Washington, D.C.|accessdate=December 31, 2018|via=[[Internet Archive]]}} {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181231033020/https://books.google.com/books?id=7JRJ-AXbTTMC&printsec=frontcover&source=gbs_ge_summary_r&cad=0#v=onepage&q&f=false|date=December 31, 2018}}\n* {{cite journal |last=Stewart |first=John |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=GgULOzNSafMC&pg=PA48#v=onepage&q&f=false |title=Early Maps and Surveyors of the City of Washington, D.C. |year=1899 |journal=Records of the Columbia Historical Society |publisher=[[Historical Society of Washington, D.C.|Columbia Historical Society]] |location=Washington, D.C. |volume=2 |pages=48\u201371 |issn=0897-9049 |oclc=40326234 |accessdate=2011-08-15 |via=[[Google Books]]}}\n* {{cite book |url=https://archive.org/details/bub_gb_D_ZJBxoCYeAC_2 |title=Standard History of the City of Washington From a Study of the Original Sources |last=Tindall |first=William |location=Knoxville, Tennessee |publisher=H. W. Crew and Company |year=1914 |lccn=14013663|oclc=7059152 |accessdate=2013-01-31 |via=[[Internet Archive]]}}\n* {{cite book |url=https://archive.org/details/sketchoflifeofbe00tyso/page/n4/mode/1up|title=A sketch of the life of Benjamin Banneker: from notes taken in 1836: read by J. Saurin Norris, before the Maryland Historical Society, October 5th, 1854 |first=Martha Ellicott |last=Tyson |location=Baltimore, Maryland|publisher=Printed for the Maryland Historical Society by John D. Toy |lccn=rc01003357|oclc=85794847|accessdate=2015-04-24|via=[[Internet Archive]]}}\n{{refend}}\n\n==External links==\n{{commons category-inline|Benjamin Banneker}}\n\n{{Portal bar|Biography|History|United States|Maryland}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Banneker, Mythology and legacy of Benjamin}}\n[[Category:African-American culture]]\n[[Category:American folklore]]\n[[Category:Misconceptions]]\n[[Category:Urban legends]]\n[[Category:Legacies by person]]\n", "name_user": "Corker1", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eBanneker's clock:remove redundant wikilink", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mythology_of_Benjamin_Banneker"}
{"title_page": "Tommy Bell (footballer, born 1923)", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2016}}\n{{Use British English|date=April 2016}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name = Tommy Bell\n| image = \n| image_size = \n| caption = \n| fullname = Thomas Anthony Peter Bell<ref name=Hugman>{{Hugman|1340|accessdate=10 April 2016}}</ref>\n| birth_date  = {{birth date|1923|12|30|df=y}}<ref name=Hugman/>\n| birth_place = [[Crompton, Lancashire|Crompton]], [[Lancashire]], England\n| death_date  = {{death date and age|1988|11|21|1923|12|30|df=y}}\n| death_place = [[Chadderton]], Lancashire, England\n| height = \n| position = [[Full back (association football)|Full back]]\n| years1 = ????\u20131946 | clubs1 = [[Glossop North End A.F.C.|Glossop]] \n| years2 = 1946      | clubs2 = [[Mossley A.F.C.|Mossley]]\n| years3 = 1946\u20131952 | clubs3 = [[Oldham Athletic A.F.C.|Oldham Athletic]] | caps3 = 170 | goals3 = 0\n| years4 = 1952\u20131953 | clubs4 = [[Stockport County F.C.|Stockport County]] | caps4 = 31  | goals4 = 0\n| years5 = 1953\u20131956 | clubs5 = [[Halifax Town A.F.C.|Halifax Town]]       | caps5 = 117 | goals5 = 1\n| years6 = 1956\u20131958 | clubs6 = [[Chorley F.C.|Chorley]]\n| years7 = 1958\u20131959 | clubs7 = [[Mossley A.F.C.|Mossley]]\n| years8 = 1959\u20131960 | clubs8 = [[Ashton United F.C.|Ashton United]]\n}}\n'''Thomas Anthony Peter Bell''' (30 December 1923 \u2013 21 November 1988) was an English professional [[association football|footballer]]. A left-back,<ref name=AZ/> he played in 318 [[The Football League|Football League]] matches for three clubs, most notably for hometown club [[Oldham Athletic A.F.C.|Oldham Athletic]]. Bell features, along with his son [[Graham Bell (footballer)|Graham]], amongst 'The Legends of Oldham Athletic'.\n\n==Career==\nBorn in [[Crompton, Lancashire|Crompton]] near Oldham, Bell signed for [[Mossley A.F.C.|Mossley]] from [[Glossop North End A.F.C.|Glossop]] in 1946.<ref name=MW>{{cite web |url=http://www.mossleyweb.com/PlayersAZ/AZB1.htm |title=Complete A-Z of Mossley players: Backhouse to Boslem |publisher=Mossley AFC |accessdate=10 April 2016}}</ref> Playing as a right-back, his performances during his 16 matches led to him signing for [[Football League Third Division North|Third Division North]] club [[Oldham Athletic]] in late 1946.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.mossleyweb.com/Statsyearbyyear/194647.htm |title=1946\u201347 |publisher=Mossley AFC |accessdate=10 April 2016}}</ref><ref name=MW/> The fee of \u00a3550 was a record for a Mossley player.<ref name=MW/>\n\nBell made his Oldham debut in their [[1946\u201347 FA Cup]] second-round defeat by [[Doncaster Rovers]] on 14 December 1946. He appears to have played well: the ''[[Daily Mirror]]'' wrote that Bell \"left the field thinking out the miserable tale he'd have to tell at home. Outside the ground was the usual mob of autograph hunters. Waiting, not for the stars of Doncaster's successful team, but for Tommy Bell, the man who played a 'blinder'.\"<ref>{{cite news |title='Look out, Bruce'\u2014Nisse |newspaper=Daily Mirror |location=London |date=16 December 1946 |page=11}}</ref>\n\nAfter playing 170 league matches for Oldham, he signed for [[Stockport County F.C.|Stockport County]] in 1952. However, the following year he left to join [[Halifax Town A.F.C.|Halifax Town]], where he remained until 1956, making 117 appearances and scoring his only goal in the Football League.<ref name=AZ>{{cite web |url=http://www.neilbrown.newcastlefans.com/player6/tommybell.html |title=Tommy Bell |website=Post War English & Scottish Football League A\u2013Z Player's Transfer Database |publisher=Neil Brown |accessdate=10 April 2016}}</ref> After leaving Halifax, he signed for [[Chorley F.C.|Chorley]], where he remained until rejoining Mossley during the 1958\u201359 season.<ref name=MW/> The final season of his playing career, 1959\u201360, saw him join [[Ashton United F.C.|Ashton United]], where he was appointed captain.<ref name=MW/>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{NeilBrownPlayers|player6/tommybell}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Bell, Tommy}}\n[[Category:1923 births]]\n[[Category:1988 deaths]]\n[[Category:English footballers]]\n[[Category:Footballers from Oldham]]\n[[Category:Glossop North End A.F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Mossley A.F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Oldham Athletic A.F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Stockport County F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Halifax Town A.F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Chorley F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Ashton United F.C. players]]\n[[Category:English Football League players]]\n[[Category:Association football defenders]]\n\n\n{{England-footy-defender-1920s-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2016}}\n{{Use British English|date=April 2016}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name = Tommy Bell\n| image = \n| image_size = \n| caption = \n| fullname = Thomas Anthony Peter Bell<ref name=Hugman>{{Hugman|1340|accessdate=10 April 2016}}</ref>\n| birth_date  = {{birth date|1923|12|30|df=y}}<ref name=Hugman/>\n| birth_place = [[Crompton, Lancashire|Crompton]], [[Lancashire]], England\n| death_date  = {{death date and age|1988|11|21|1923|12|30|df=y}}\n| death_place = [[Chadderton]], Lancashire, England\n| height = \n| position = [[Full back (association football)|Full back]]\n| years1 = ????\u20131946 | clubs1 = [[Glossop North End A.F.C.|Glossop]] \n| years2 = 1946      | clubs2 = [[Mossley A.F.C.|Mossley]]\n| years3 = 1946\u20131952 | clubs3 = [[Oldham Athletic A.F.C.|Oldham Athletic]] | caps3 = 170 | goals3 = 0\n| years4 = 1952\u20131953 | clubs4 = [[Stockport County F.C.|Stockport County]] | caps4 = 31  | goals4 = 0\n| years5 = 1953\u20131956 | clubs5 = [[Halifax Town A.F.C.|Halifax Town]]       | caps5 = 117 | goals5 = 1\n| years6 = 1956\u20131958 | clubs6 = [[Chorley F.C.|Chorley]]\n| years7 = 1958\u20131959 | clubs7 = [[Mossley A.F.C.|Mossley]]\n| years8 = 1959\u20131960 | clubs8 = [[Ashton United F.C.|Ashton United]]\n}}\n'''Thomas Anthony Peter Bell''' (30 December 1923 \u2013 21 November 1988) was an English professional [[association football|footballer]]. A left-back,<ref name=AZ/> he played in 318 [[The Football League|Football League]] matches for three clubs, most notably for hometown club [[Oldham Athletic A.F.C.|Oldham Athletic]]. Bell features, along with his son [[Graham Bell (footballer)|Graham]], amongst 'The Legends of Oldham Athletic'.\n\n==Career==\nBorn in [[Crompton, Lancashire|Crompton]] near Oldham, Bell signed for [[Mossley A.F.C.|Mossley]] from [[Glossop North End A.F.C.|Glossop]] in 1946.<ref name=MW>{{cite web |url=http://www.mossleyweb.com/PlayersAZ/AZB1.htm |title=Complete A-Z of Mossley players: Backhouse to Boslem |publisher=Mossley AFC |accessdate=10 April 2016}}</ref> Playing as a right-back, his performances during his 16 matches led to him signing for [[Football League Third Division North|Third Division North]] club [[Oldham Athletic]] in late 1946.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.mossleyweb.com/Statsyearbyyear/194647.htm |title=1946\u201347 |publisher=Mossley AFC |accessdate=10 April 2016}}</ref><ref name=MW/> The fee of \u00a3550 was a record for a Mossley player.<ref name=MW/>\n\nBell made his Oldham debut in their [[1946\u201347 FA Cup]] second-round defeat by [[Doncaster Rovers]] on 14 December 1946. He appears to have played well: the ''[[Daily Mirror]]'' wrote that Bell \"left the field thinking out the miserable tale he'd have to tell at home. Outside the ground was the usual mob of autograph hunters. Waiting, not for the stars of Doncaster's successful team, but for Tommy Bell, the man who played a 'blinder'.\"<ref>{{cite news |title='Look out, Bruce'\u2014Nisse |newspaper=Daily Mirror |location=London |date=16 December 1946 |page=11}}</ref>\n\nAfter playing 170 league matches for Oldham, he signed for [[Stockport County F.C.|Stockport County]] in 1952. However, the following year he left to join [[Halifax Town A.F.C.|Halifax Town]], where he remained until 1956, making 117 appearances and scoring his only goal in the Football League.<ref name=AZ>{{cite web |url=http://www.neilbrown.newcastlefans.com/player6/tommybell.html |title=Tommy Bell |website=Post War English & Scottish Football League A\u2013Z Player's Transfer Database |publisher=Neil Brown |accessdate=10 April 2016}}</ref> After leaving Halifax, he signed for [[Chorley F.C.|Chorley]], where he remained until rejoining Mossley during the 1958\u201359 season.<ref name=MW/> The final season of his playing career, 1959\u201360, saw him join [[Ashton United F.C.|Ashton United]], where he was appointed captain.<ref name=MW/>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{NeilBrownPlayers|player6/tommybell}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Bell, Tommy}}\n[[Category:1923 births]]\n[[Category:1988 deaths]]\n[[Category:English footballers]]\n[[Category:Footballers from Oldham]]\n[[Category:Glossop North End A.F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Mossley A.F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Oldham Athletic A.F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Stockport County F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Halifax Town A.F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Chorley F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Ashton United F.C. players]]\n[[Category:English Football League players]]\n\n\n[[Category:Association football defenders]]\n{{England-footy-defender-1920s-stub}}\n", "name_user": "GiantSnowman", "label": "safe", "comment": "clean up", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tommy_Bell_(footballer,_born_1923)"}
{"title_page": "Tommy Bell (footballer, born 1906)", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2016}}\n{{Use British English|date=April 2016}}\n{{more citations needed|date=September 2016}}\n\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name = Tommy Bell\n| image = \n| fullname = Thomas Bell\n| birth_date = {{birth date|1906|11|9|df=y}}\n| birth_place = [[Seaham Harbour]], England\n| death_date = {{death year and age|1983|1906}}\n| height = \n| position = [[Forward (association football)|Forward]] / [[right half]]\n| years1 =   \n| clubs1 = [[Dawdon Colliery Welfare F.C.|Dawdon Colliery]] \n| years2 = 1924\u20131926 \n| clubs2 = [[Bristol City F.C.|Bristol City]] \n| caps2 = 0  \n| goals2 = 0\n| years3 = 1924 \n| clubs3 = \u2192 [[Torquay United F.C.|Torquay United]] (loan) \n| caps3 =   \n| goals3 =   \n| years4 = 1926\u20131927 \n| clubs4 = [[Merthyr Town F.C.|Merthyr Town]] \n| caps4 =  10   \n| goals4 =  1  \n| years5 = 1927\u20131930 \n| clubs5 = [[Halifax Town A.F.C.|Halifax Town]] \n| caps5 =  89  \n| goals5 =  26  \n| years6 = 1930\u20131931 \n| clubs6 = [[Chesterfield F.C.|Chesterfield]] \n| caps6 =  55  \n| goals6 =  22  \n| years7 = 1931\u20131933 \n| clubs7 = [[Southport F.C.|Southport]] \n| caps7 =  47   \n| goals7 =  6  \n| years8 = 1933\u20131934 \n| clubs8 = [[Luton Town F.C.|Luton Town]] \n| caps8 =  34  \n| goals8 =  15  \n| years9 = 1934\u20131938\n| caps9 =  73  \n| goals9 =  31 \n| clubs9 = [[Northampton Town F.C.|Northampton Town]] \n| clubs10= [[Wellingborough Town F.C.|Wellingborough Town]] \n| clubs11= [[Spalding United F.C.|Spalding United]]\n}}\n'''Thomas Bell''' (9 November 1906 \u2013 1983) was an English professional [[association football|footballer]] born in [[Seaham Harbour]]. He could play at [[inside right]], [[centre forward]] and [[right half]] and was a regular goalscorer throughout his professional career.\n\nBell played for [[Dawdon Colliery Welfare F.C.|Dawdon Colliery]] before joining [[Bristol City F.C.|Bristol City]]. Unable to break into the City first team, Bell joined [[Torquay United F.C.|Torquay United]] on loan, playing at centre-forward in their three [[FA Cup]] ties in the 1924\u20131925 season. He failed to appear in the league for Bristol City and joined [[Merthyr Town F.C.|Merthyr Town]] in 1926. He subsequently played for [[Halifax Town A.F.C.|Halifax Town]], [[Chesterfield F.C.|Chesterfield]], [[Southport F.C.|Southport]], [[Luton Town F.C.|Luton Town]] and [[Northampton Town F.C.|Northampton Town]] before playing non-league football for [[Wellingborough Town F.C.|Wellingborough Town]] and [[Spalding United F.C.|Spalding United]].<ref>{{cite book |last=Joyce |first=Michael |title=Football League Players' Records 1888 to 1939 |publisher=SoccerData |location=Nottingham |date=2004 |page=23 |isbn=978-1-899468-67-6}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Bell, Tommy}}\n[[Category:1906 births]]\n[[Category:1983 deaths]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Seaham]]\n[[Category:English footballers]]\n[[Category:Association football forwards]]\n[[Category:Association football wing halves]]\n[[Category:Dawdon Colliery Welfare F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Bristol City F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Torquay United F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Merthyr Town F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Halifax Town A.F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Chesterfield F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Southport F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Luton Town F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Northampton Town F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Wellingborough Town F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Spalding United F.C. players]]\n[[Category:English Football League players]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2016}}\n{{Use British English|date=April 2016}}\n{{refimprove|date=September 2016}}\n\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name = Tommy Bell\n| image = \n| fullname = Thomas Bell\n| birth_date = {{birth date|1906|11|9|df=y}}\n| birth_place = [[Seaham Harbour]], England\n| death_date = {{death year and age|1983|1906}}\n| height = \n| position = [[Forward (association football)|Forward]] / [[right half]]\n| years1 =   \n| clubs1 = [[Dawdon Colliery Welfare F.C.|Dawdon Colliery]] \n| years2 = 1924\u20131926 \n| clubs2 = [[Bristol City F.C.|Bristol City]] \n| caps2 = 0  \n| goals2 = 0\n| years3 = 1924 \n| clubs3 = \u2192 [[Torquay United F.C.|Torquay United]] (loan) \n| caps3 =   \n| goals3 =   \n| years4 = 1926\u20131927 \n| clubs4 = [[Merthyr Town F.C.|Merthyr Town]] \n| caps4 =  10   \n| goals4 =  1  \n| years5 = 1927\u20131930 \n| clubs5 = [[Halifax Town A.F.C.|Halifax Town]] \n| caps5 =  89  \n| goals5 =  26  \n| years6 = 1930\u20131931 \n| clubs6 = [[Chesterfield F.C.|Chesterfield]] \n| caps6 =  55  \n| goals6 =  22  \n| years7 = 1931\u20131933 \n| clubs7 = [[Southport F.C.|Southport]] \n| caps7 =  47   \n| goals7 =  6  \n| years8 = 1933\u20131934 \n| clubs8 = [[Luton Town F.C.|Luton Town]] \n| caps8 =  34  \n| goals8 =  15  \n| years9 = 1934\u20131938\n| caps9 =  73  \n| goals9 =  31 \n| clubs9 = [[Northampton Town F.C.|Northampton Town]] \n| clubs10= [[Wellingborough Town F.C.|Wellingborough Town]] \n| clubs11= [[Spalding United F.C.|Spalding United]]\n}}\n'''Thomas Bell''' (9 November 1906 \u2013 1983) was an English professional [[association football|footballer]] born in [[Seaham Harbour]]. He could play at [[inside right]], [[centre forward]] and [[right half]] and was a regular goalscorer throughout his professional career.\n\nBell played for [[Dawdon Colliery Welfare F.C.|Dawdon Colliery]] before joining [[Bristol City F.C.|Bristol City]]. Unable to break into the City first team, Bell joined [[Torquay United F.C.|Torquay United]] on loan, playing at centre-forward in their three [[FA Cup]] ties in the 1924-1925 season. He failed to appear in the league for Bristol City and joined [[Merthyr Town F.C.|Merthyr Town]] in 1926. He subsequently played for [[Halifax Town A.F.C.|Halifax Town]], [[Chesterfield F.C.|Chesterfield]], [[Southport F.C.|Southport]], [[Luton Town F.C.|Luton Town]] and [[Northampton Town F.C.|Northampton Town]] before playing non-league football for [[Wellingborough Town F.C.|Wellingborough Town]] and [[Spalding United F.C.|Spalding United]].<ref>{{cite book |last=Joyce |first=Michael |title=Football League Players' Records 1888 to 1939 |publisher=SoccerData |location=Nottingham |date=2004 |page=23 |isbn=978-1-899468-67-6}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Bell, Tommy}}\n[[Category:1906 births]]\n[[Category:1983 deaths]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Seaham]]\n[[Category:English footballers]]\n[[Category:Association football forwards]]\n[[Category:Association football wing halves]]\n[[Category:Dawdon Colliery Welfare F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Bristol City F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Torquay United F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Merthyr Town F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Halifax Town A.F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Chesterfield F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Southport F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Luton Town F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Northampton Town F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Wellingborough Town F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Spalding United F.C. players]]\n[[Category:English Football League players]]\n", "name_user": "GiantSnowman", "label": "safe", "comment": "clean up,typo(s) fixed: 1924-1925 \u2192 1924\u20131925", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tommy_Bell_(footballer,_born_1906)"}
{"title_page": "Tommy Becton", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2016}}\n{{Use British English|date=April 2016}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name          = Tommy Becton\n| image          = \n| caption        = \n| fullname       = Thomas Becton\n| birth_date    = 1878\n| birth_place = [[Preston, Lancashire|Preston]], England\n| death_date    = {{death date|1957|8|11|df=y}} (aged 78\u201379)\n| death_place = [[Fulwood, Lancashire|Fulwood]], England\n| height         = \n| position       = [[Inside forward|Inside left]]/[[Outside forward|Outside left]]\n| years1         = 1897\u20131898 |clubs1=[[Preston North End F.C.|Preston North End]] |caps1=4 |goals1=0\n| years2         = 1898\u20131899 |clubs2=[[New Brighton Tower F.C.|New Brighton Tower]] |caps2=24 |goals2=7\n| years3         = 1899\u20131900 |clubs3=[[Sunderland A.F.C.|Sunderland]] |caps3=14 |goals3=7\n| years4         = 1900\u20131901 |clubs4=[[Kettering Town F.C.|Kettering Town]] |caps4= |goals4=\n| years5         = 1901\u20131902 |clubs5=[[Bristol Rovers F.C.|Bristol Rovers]] |caps5=25 |goals5=3\n| years6         = 1902\u2013? |clubs6=[[Kettering Town F.C.|Kettering Town]] |caps6= |goals6=\n| years7         = {{0|000}} |clubs7=[[Oswaldtwistle Rovers F.C.|Oswaldtwistle Rovers]] |caps7= |goals7=\n| years8         = {{0|000}} |clubs8=[[Colne F.C.|Colne]] |caps8= |goals8=\n| years9         = {{0|000}} |clubs9=[[Rossendale United F.C.|Rossendale United]] |caps9= |goals9=\n}}\n'''Thomas Becton''' (1878\u201311 August 1957) was a professional [[association football|footballer]], who played in [[The Football League]] for [[Preston North End F.C.|Preston North End]], [[New Brighton Tower F.C.|New Brighton Tower]] and [[Sunderland A.F.C.|Sunderland]], as well as playing professionally for a number of teams outside the Football League.\n\nBecton was a [[forward (association football)|forward]], who played in the [[Inside forward|inside left]] and [[Outside forward|outside left]] positions, starting out with his home town club, Preston North End. He moved to the now-defunct New Brighton Tower in 1898, and to Sunderland a year later.<ref name=Joyce>{{cite book |last1=Joyce |first1=Michael |title=Football League Players' Records 1888\u20131939 |year=2004 |publisher=SoccerData |location=[[Nottingham]] |isbn=1-899468-67-6 |page=21}}</ref> Following this he played for a series of non-Football League clubs, starting with [[Kettering Town F.C.|Kettering Town]] in 1900. He moved to [[Southern Football League|Southern League]] side [[Bristol Rovers F.C.|Bristol Rovers]] in 1901, before returning to Kettering after a year.<ref>{{cite book |last1=Byrne |first1=Stephen |last2=Jay |first2=Mike |title=Bristol Rovers Football Club - The Definitive History 1883-2003 |year=2003 |publisher=[[Tempus Publishing|Tempus]] |location=[[Stroud, Gloucestershire|Stroud]] |isbn=0-7524-2717-2 |page=489}}</ref>\n\nHe went on to play for [[Oswaldtwistle Rovers F.C.|Oswaldtwistle Rovers]] and [[Colne F.C.|Colne]], and ended his career playing with [[Rossendale United F.C.|Rossendale United]].<ref name=Joyce/>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Becton, Tommy}}\n[[Category:1878 births]]\n[[Category:1957 deaths]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Preston, Lancashire]]\n[[Category:English footballers]]\n[[Category:Association football forwards]]\n[[Category:English Football League players]]\n[[Category:Southern Football League players]]\n[[Category:Preston North End F.C. players]]\n[[Category:New Brighton Tower F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Sunderland A.F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Kettering Town F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Bristol Rovers F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Colne F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Rossendale United F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Oswaldtwistle Rovers F.C. players]]\n\n\n{{England-footy-forward-1870s-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2016}}\n{{Use British English|date=April 2016}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name          = Tommy Becton\n| image          = \n| caption        = \n| fullname       = Thomas Becton\n| birth_date    = 1878\n| birth_place = [[Preston, Lancashire|Preston]], England\n| death_date    = {{death date|1957|8|11|df=y}} (aged 78\u201379)\n| death_place = [[Fulwood, Lancashire|Fulwood]], England\n| height         = \n| position       = [[Inside forward|Inside left]]/[[Outside forward|Outside left]]\n| years1         = 1897\u20131898 |clubs1=[[Preston North End F.C.|Preston North End]] |caps1=4 |goals1=0\n| years2         = 1898\u20131899 |clubs2=[[New Brighton Tower F.C.|New Brighton Tower]] |caps2=24 |goals2=7\n| years3         = 1899\u20131900 |clubs3=[[Sunderland A.F.C.|Sunderland]] |caps3=14 |goals3=7\n| years4         = 1900\u20131901 |clubs4=[[Kettering Town F.C.|Kettering Town]] |caps4= |goals4=\n| years5         = 1901\u20131902 |clubs5=[[Bristol Rovers F.C.|Bristol Rovers]] |caps5=25 |goals5=3\n| years6         = 1902\u2013? |clubs6=[[Kettering Town F.C.|Kettering Town]] |caps6= |goals6=\n| years7         = {{0|000}}?\u2013? |clubs7=[[Oswaldtwistle Rovers F.C.|Oswaldtwistle Rovers]] |caps7= |goals7=\n| years8         = {{0|000}}?\u2013? |clubs8=[[Colne F.C.|Colne]] |caps8= |goals8=\n| years9         = {{0|000}}?\u2013? |clubs9=[[Rossendale United F.C.|Rossendale United]] |caps9= |goals9=\n}}\n'''Thomas Becton''' (1878\u201311 August 1957) was a professional [[association football|footballer]], who played in [[The Football League]] for [[Preston North End F.C.|Preston North End]], [[New Brighton Tower F.C.|New Brighton Tower]] and [[Sunderland A.F.C.|Sunderland]], as well as playing professionally for a number of teams outside the Football League.\n\nBecton was a [[forward (association football)|forward]], who played in the [[Inside forward|inside left]] and [[Outside forward|outside left]] positions, starting out with his home town club, Preston North End. He moved to the now-defunct New Brighton Tower in 1898, and to Sunderland a year later.<ref name=Joyce>{{cite book |last1=Joyce |first1=Michael |title=Football League Players' Records 1888\u20131939 |year=2004 |publisher=SoccerData |location=[[Nottingham]] |isbn=1-899468-67-6 |page=21}}</ref> Following this he played for a series of non-Football League clubs, starting with [[Kettering Town F.C.|Kettering Town]] in 1900. He moved to [[Southern Football League|Southern League]] side [[Bristol Rovers F.C.|Bristol Rovers]] in 1901, before returning to Kettering after a year.<ref>{{cite book |last1=Byrne |first1=Stephen |last2=Jay |first2=Mike |title=Bristol Rovers Football Club - The Definitive History 1883-2003 |year=2003 |publisher=[[Tempus Publishing|Tempus]] |location=[[Stroud, Gloucestershire|Stroud]] |isbn=0-7524-2717-2 |page=489}}</ref>\n\nHe went on to play for [[Oswaldtwistle Rovers F.C.|Oswaldtwistle Rovers]] and [[Colne F.C.|Colne]], and ended his career playing with [[Rossendale United F.C.|Rossendale United]].<ref name=Joyce/>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Becton, Tommy}}\n[[Category:1878 births]]\n[[Category:1957 deaths]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Preston, Lancashire]]\n[[Category:English footballers]]\n[[Category:Association football forwards]]\n[[Category:English Football League players]]\n[[Category:Southern Football League players]]\n[[Category:Preston North End F.C. players]]\n[[Category:New Brighton Tower F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Sunderland A.F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Kettering Town F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Bristol Rovers F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Colne F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Rossendale United F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Oswaldtwistle Rovers F.C. players]]\n\n\n{{England-footy-forward-1870s-stub}}\n", "name_user": "GiantSnowman", "label": "safe", "comment": "clean up", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tommy_Becton"}
